thread.title_full: New song reviews: One Direction, Gwen Stefani and Fall Out Boy with Demi Lovato

title: New song reviews: One Direction, Gwen Stefani and Fall Out Boy with Demi Lovato
text:
Gwen Stefani 
Single: "Used to Love You" 
Gut reaction: After last December's annoying "Spark the Fire" failed to catch fire, Stefani channels '80s pop and looks inward for this brokenhearted ballad almost certainly related to her divorce from Bush rocker Gavin Rossdale. It won't put her on top of the pop charts again, but it should remind some people why they used to love her. 
Grade: B Fall Out Boy featuring Demi Lovato 
Single: "Irresistible" 
Gut reaction: "Irresistible" has been out for a while now, but Fall Out Boy (featuring Menomonee Falls native Andy Hurley on drums) has re-released the song with guest vocals from Demi Lovato. Adding her aggressive vocals, well-matched with lead singer Patrick Stump's melodramatic delivery, is definitely an improvement. 
Grade: B- •••
